answers.body_markdown:
That&#39;s because `typeof x.a` is actually a string. Here, x is constant but the value of `x.a` can be changed to any string value.

If the value of `x.a` is not going to change then a possible solution(using [const assertion][1] added in typescript version 3.4):
```
const x = {
    a: &#39;c&#39;,
    b: &#39;d&#39;
} as const;

const y = {
    [x.a]: &#39;e&#39;,
}

typeof y -&gt; {
    c: string
}
```


  [1]: https://www.typescriptlang.org/docs/handbook/release-notes/typescript-3-4.html#const-assertions

